+but is needed to obtain a uniform-in-$h$ bound on
+$\partial_t\hat\bM_{h,\ddt}$ in a negative-order space and hence
+to apply the Aubin--Lions theorem to the magnetization.
+In two dimensions, \eqref{eq:M_L4} can equivalently be enforced by
+adding a small $\eta\,\|\nabla\bM^k\|^2_{L^2}$ stabilization term
+to the Cahn--Hilliard--magnetization coupling at the cost of
+modifying the consistency analysis; we work directly under
+Assumption~\ref{ass:M_L4} to keep the scheme as stated in
+Section~\ref{sec:scheme}.
+\end{assumption}
